1.comment: Colin Baxter continuously botched snaps. Sanchez's protection was awful, as he was under pressure on nearly every single pass attempt. As a result, Sanchez went 11-of-35 for 119 yards, a pick and 4 fumbles, 2 of which were returned for touchdowns. The run blocking was non-existent as well.
